bcl:definition.bcl:text:
collection agent has the same meaning as in section
  125 [definitions] of the Act, but does not include a
bailiff;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
insurance agents licensed under the Financial Institutions
              Act, in respect of the collection of insurance
          premiums;

discounters, as defined in section 2 of the Tax Rebate Discounting
            Act (Canada), exercising rights to refunds of tax acquired from
          taxpayers;
